title: 3476 pp5v_S5 pulsing 5-3-5-3-5 etc
message: 820-3476 Presented with no liquid damage, however r5193 an r5699 were blown, and pad on r5193 pp3v42 was gone. Ran a jumper to it.  still no fan spin. Started through the rails. pp5v_s5 seems to be pulsing betwixt 5 and 3 volts... not normal is it?

title: 3476 pp5v_S5 pulsing 5-3-5-3-5 etc
message: Those resistors don't "blow" This was a liquid damage case. G2_EN is probably pulsing, is S5_PWRGD pulsing too?

title: 3476 pp5v_S5 pulsing 5-3-5-3-5 etc
message:
[QUOTE="dukefawks, post: 27728"]Those resistors don't "blow" This was a liquid damage case. G2_EN is probably pulsing, is S5_PWRGD pulsing too?[/QUOTE]

It's hard to say liquid damage. But I did mean corrosion on those two when I said "blow". It would be weird because there is no other evidence of liquid infiltration. Just those two little r's. Nonetheless S5_PWRGD  and G2_EN are both pulsing all over the place.

title: 3476 pp5v_S5 pulsing 5-3-5-3-5 etc
message: Check for short on 3V3_S5, else it could be crap under SMC or bad TPS51980.
